value.value: Liquid preparation consisting of a solution intended for veterinary use by dipping.
Liquid preparation consisting of a suspension intended for veterinary use by dipping.
Administration of a veterinary medicinal product by immersing the animal into a bath or plunge pool containing the medicinal product.

label.value: Dispersible Tablet for Dose Dispenser Dosage Form

value.value: Solid preparation consisting of small, dispersible tablets that are designed to be used in a dose dispenser, each tablet usually consisting of a small fraction of a dose, with multiple tablets being automatically counted and administered as a single dose.

label.value: Dispersion for Concentrate for Dispersion for Infusion Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid sterile preparation consisting of a dispersion intended for use in the preparation of a concentrate for dispersion for infusion, which in turn is intended to be diluted in the specified liquid to obtain a dispersion for infusion.

label.value: DS Falconer, Edinburgh, Non-obese Inbred Stock

value.value: Liquid sterile preparation consisting of two or more phases of which at least one is dispersed in the liquid phase, intended to be introduced, usually in large volumes, usually into the circulating blood stream.
Liquid sterile preparation consisting of two or more phases of which at least one is dispersed in the liquid phase, intended for administration by injection.
Sterile liquid preparation consisting of two or more phases of which at least one is dispersed in the liquid phase, intended for administration by injection or infusion.
Container intended for use in a dose dispenser, usually pre-filled with a medicinal product.
Closure with dredging device.
Container for a pharmaceutical form to be applied by dredging.
Device for administering an oral liquid to an animal.
A unit of presentation used to represent the quantity of product that is found in a single discrete entity where the pharmaceutical dose form is a type of dressing.
Screw cap with dropper.
A container, usually a bottle, fitted with a dropper applicator.

Liquid single-dose or multidose preparation consisting of an emulsion intended for application to the external auditory meatus. Multidose containers may be dropper containers or containers provided with a dropper applicator, or the dropper may be supplied separately. Drops are not necessarily administered dropwise, but may also be administered as a small volume.

label.value: Ear drops, Powder for Suspension Dosage Form

value.value: Powder and solvent intended for the preparation of ear drops, suspension, by dispersing the powder in the solvent.

label.value: Ear Drops Powder for Suspension Dosage Form

value.value: Solid preparation consisting of one or more powder intended to be dispersed in the specified liquid to obtain an ear drops suspension.

Liquid single-dose or multidose preparation consisting of an aqueous or oily solution intended for application to the external auditory meatus. Multidose containers may be dropper containers or containers provided with a dropper applicator, or the dropper may be supplied separately. Drops are not necessarily administered dropwise, but may also be administered as a small volume.
Semi-solid single-dose or multidose preparation consisting of a gel intended for application to the external auditory meatus, if necessary by means of a tampon impregnated with the preparation.

Liquid single-dose or multidose preparation consisting of an aqueous or oily suspension intended for application to the external auditory meatus. Multidose containers may be dropper containers or containers provided with a dropper applicator, or the dropper may be supplied separately. Drops are not necessarily administered dropwise, but may also be administered as a small volume.

label.value: Ear Drops, Suspension in Single-dose Container Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of an ear drops suspension presented in a single-dose container.
Semi-solid single-dose or multidose preparation consisting of an ointment intended for application to the external auditory meatus, if necessary by means of a tampon impregnated with the preparation.

Solid, usually multidose preparation consisting of one or more powders consisting of (a) solid active substance(s) intended for application to the external auditory meatus. Ear powders are presented in containers fitted with a suitable applicator or device for insufflation.

Liquid, usually multidose preparation consisting of an emulsion intended for application to the external auditory meatus by spraying to obtain local effect. Ear sprays are presented in containers with a spray pump or in pressurized containers fitted with a spray valve.

label.value: Random Inbred Stock JC DeFries, Inst Behav Genet, Colorado

value.value: Liquid, usually multidose preparation consisting of a solution intended for application to the external auditory meatus by spraying to obtain a local effect. Ear sprays are presented in containers with a spray pump or in pressurized containers fitted with a spray valve.

Liquid, usually multidose preparation consisting of a suspension intended for application to the external auditory meatus by spraying to obtain a local effect. Ear sprays are presented in containers with a spray pump or in pressurized containers fitted with a spray valve.
Solid single-dose preparation of usually conical shape intended to be inserted in the external auditory meatus where it melts or dissolves.

Solid preparation consisting of a matrix impregnated with active substance(s), which is fixed to a device to be tagged on the animal's ear. The active substance(s) are released by diffusion, by mechanical means or by vaporization over a period of time.
Solid single-dose preparation intended to be inserted into the external auditory meatus for a limited period of time, consisting of a suitable material impregnated with active substance(s).
Liquid single-dose or multidose preparation consisting usually of an oil-in-water emulsion with a pH within physiological limits. Ear washes are intended to clean the external auditory meatus.
Liquid single-dose or multidose preparation consisting usually of an aqueous solution with a pH within physiological limits. Ear washes are intended to clean the external auditory meatus.
Liquid sterile preparation consisting of a solution intended for use as ear drops or eye drops.
Liquid sterile preparation consisting of a suspension intended for use as ear drops or eye drops.
Semi-solid preparation consisting of an ointment intended for auricular or ocular use.
Liquid sterile preparation consisting of a solution intended for use as ear drops, eye drops or nasal drops.
Liquid preparation consisting of a suspension intended for use as ear drops or nasal drops.

label.value: Effervescent Granules plus Film-Coated Tablet Dosage Form

value.value: Combination package consisting of effervescent granules and a film-coated tablet.

label.value: Effervescent Granules for Oral Suspension Dosage Form

value.value: Solid preparation consisting of effervescent granules intended to be dispersed or dissolved in the specified liquid, which is supplied in the same packaging, to obtain an oral suspension.

label.value: Effervescent Tablet plus Film-Coated Tablet Dosage Form

value.value: Combination package consisting of an effervescent tablet and a film-coated tablet.

Solid single-dose preparation consisting of a vaginal tablet usually containing acid substances and carbonates or hydrogen carbonates that react rapidly in the presence of aqueous liquid to release carbon dioxide.

label.value: Emulsion and Lyophilisate for Suspension for Injection Dosage Form

value.value: Sterile emulsion and sterile lyophilisate (freeze-dried powder) intended for the preparation of a suspension for injection, for veterinary use, by dispersing the lyophilisate in the emulsion. The emulsion contains active ingredient(s); the lyophilisate may or may not contain active ingredient(s).

label.value: Emulsion and Suspension for Emulsion for Injection Dosage Form

value.value: Sterile emulsion and sterile suspension, both of which contain active substance(s), intended for the preparation of an emulsion for injection by mixing the emulsion and the suspension.

label.value: Emulsion for Emulsion for Injection Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid sterile preparation consisting of an emulsion intended for use in the preparation of an emulsion for injection.
Liquid sterile preparation consisting of an oil-in-water emulsion intended to be introduced, usually in large volumes, usually into the circulating blood stream.
